The paper discusses a bio-inspired artificial neural network architecture that models the affective aspects of brain function. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the network for pattern recognition and classification of images, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the network for non-local salience effects, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
